description:
Update claim command for absolute paths in global storage.

## Current Implementation
- Claims stored with project-relative paths
- Matched against project-relative file paths

## New Implementation
- Claims stored with absolute paths
- Input: relative paths auto-expanded from cwd
- Display: relative when in same tree, absolute otherwise

## Path Handling
```rust
fn expand_claim_pattern(pattern: &str) -> Result<String> {
    let cwd = std::env::current_dir()?;
    if pattern.starts_with('/') {
        // Already absolute
        Ok(pattern.to_string())
    } else {
        // Expand relative to cwd
        Ok(cwd.join(pattern).to_string_lossy().to_string())
    }
}

fn display_claim_pattern(pattern: &str) -> String {
    let cwd = std::env::current_dir().ok();
    if let Some(cwd) = cwd {
        if let Ok(rel) = Path::new(pattern).strip_prefix(&cwd) {
            return rel.to_string_lossy().to_string();
        }
    }
    pattern.to_string()
}
```

## Commands
```bash
# Relative input (common case)
cd ~/src/botbus
botbus claim "src/**/*.rs"
# Stored as: /home/user/src/botbus/src/**/*.rs

# Absolute input (explicit)
botbus claim "/home/user/src/botbus/src/**/*.rs"

# Display adapts to context
cd ~/src/botbus
botbus claims
# Shows: src/**/*.rs (you're in the same tree)

cd ~/src/other
botbus claims  
# Shows: /home/user/src/botbus/src/**/*.rs (different location)
```

## check-claim
Same expansion logic:
```bash
cd ~/src/botbus
botbus check-claim src/main.rs
# Expands to /home/user/src/botbus/src/main.rs for matching
```

## Claims File
Location: ~/.local/share/botbus/claims.jsonl
Format unchanged, just paths are now absolute.

Rewrite src/core/project.rs to use XDG-based global paths instead of per-project .botbus/ directories.

## Current Implementation
- `BOTBUS_DIR = '.botbus'`
- `find_project_root()` walks up looking for .botbus/
- All paths relative to project_root

## New Implementation
```rust
use directories::ProjectDirs;

pub fn botbus_data_dir() -> PathBuf {
    // Returns ~/.local/share/botbus/ on Linux
    // Uses XDG_DATA_HOME if set
    ProjectDirs::from("", "", "botbus")
        .map(|dirs| dirs.data_dir().to_path_buf())
        .unwrap_or_else(|| {
            dirs::home_dir()
                .unwrap_or_else(|| PathBuf::from("."))
                .join(".local/share/botbus")
        })
}

pub fn ensure_data_dir() -> Result<PathBuf> {
    let dir = botbus_data_dir();
    fs::create_dir_all(&dir)?;
    fs::create_dir_all(channels_dir())?;
    Ok(dir)
}

pub fn channels_dir() -> PathBuf {
    botbus_data_dir().join("channels")
}

pub fn channel_path(channel: &str) -> PathBuf {
    channels_dir().join(format!("{}.jsonl", channel))
}

pub fn claims_path() -> PathBuf {
    botbus_data_dir().join("claims.jsonl")
}

pub fn state_path() -> PathBuf {
    botbus_data_dir().join("state.json")
}

pub fn index_path() -> PathBuf {
    botbus_data_dir().join("index.sqlite")
}
```

## Functions to Remove
- `find_project_root()` - no longer needed
- `botbus_dir(project_root)` - replaced by `botbus_data_dir()`
- `agents_path()` - no agents.jsonl in new design
- `BOTBUS_DIR` constant

## New Function
- `ensure_data_dir()` - creates data dir and channels subdir if needed

## Dependencies
The `directories` crate is already in Cargo.toml

